{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://docs.ghost.org","title":"Ghost Docs","description":"Everything you need to know about working with the Ghost professional publishing platform."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Ghost Security","date":null,"date_pretty":null,"path":null,"meta_title":"Security and Privacy","meta_description":"Ghost is committed to developing secure, reliable products utilising all modern security best practices. Find out more about our security and privacy.","image":null,"next":null,"sidebar":"concepts","toc":null,"keywords":["concepts","ghost","publishing","security"]},"html":"<p>Ghost is committed to developing secure, reliable products utilising all modern security best practices and processes.</p>\n<p>The Ghost security team is made up of full time staff employed by the Ghost Foundation as well as volunteer open source contributors and security experts. We do both consultation and penetration testing of our software and infrastructure with external security researchers and agencies.</p>\n<p>We take security very seriously at Ghost and welcome any peer review of our completely <a href=\"https://github.com/tryghost/ghost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">open source codebase</a> to help ensure that it remains completely secure.</p>\n<h2 id=\"security-features\"><a href=\"#security-features\" aria-label=\"security features permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Security features</h2>\n<h3 id=\"automatic-ssl\"><a href=\"#automatic-ssl\" aria-label=\"automatic ssl permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Automatic SSL</h3>\n<p>Ghost's CLI tool attempts to automatically configure SSL certificates for all new Ghost installs with Let's Encrypt by default. In 2019 we intend to make SSL mandatory for all new installs.</p>\n<h3 id=\"standardised-permissions\"><a href=\"#standardised-permissions\" aria-label=\"standardised permissions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Standardised permissions</h3>\n<p>Ghost-CLI does not run as <code class=\"language-text\">root</code> and automatically configures all server directory permissions correctly according to <a href=\"https://www.owasp.org/index.php/File_System\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">OWASP Standards</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"brute-force-protection\"><a href=\"#brute-force-protection\" aria-label=\"brute force protection permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Brute force protection</h3>\n<p>User login attempts and password reset requests are all limited to 5 per hour per IP.</p>\n<h3 id=\"data-validation-and-serialisation\"><a href=\"#data-validation-and-serialisation\" aria-label=\"data validation and serialisation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data validation and serialisation</h3>\n<p>Ghost performs strong serialisation and validation on all data that goes into the database, as well as automated symlink protection on all uploaded files.</p>\n<h3 id=\"encoded-tokens-everywhere\"><a href=\"#encoded-tokens-everywhere\" aria-label=\"encoded tokens everywhere permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Encoded tokens everywhere</h3>\n<p>All user invitation and password reset tokens are base64 encoded with serverside secret. All tokens are always single use and always expire.</p>\n<h3 id=\"password-hashing\"><a href=\"#password-hashing\" aria-label=\"password hashing permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Password hashing</h3>\n<p>Ghost follows <a href=\"https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10-2017_A2-Broken_Authentication\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">OWASP authentication standards</a> with all passwords hashed and salted properly using <code class=\"language-text\">bcrypt</code> to ensure password integrity.</p>\n<h3 id=\"sqli-prevention\"><a href=\"#sqli-prevention\" aria-label=\"sqli prevention permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>SQLi prevention</h3>\n<p>Ghost uses <a href=\"http://bookshelfjs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Bookshelf</a> ORM + <a href=\"https://knexjs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Knex</a> query builder and does not generate <em>any</em> of its own raw SQL queries. Ghost has no interpolation of variables directly to SQL strings.</p>\n<h3 id=\"xss-prevention\"><a href=\"#xss-prevention\" aria-label=\"xss prevention permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>XSS prevention</h3>\n<p>Ghost uses safe/escaped strings used everywhere, including and especially in all custom Handlebars helpers used in <a href=\"/api/handlebars-themes/\">Ghost Themes</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"dependency-management\"><a href=\"#dependency-management\" aria-label=\"dependency management permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dependency management</h3>\n<p>All Ghost dependencies are continually scanned with <a href=\"https://github.com/nodesecurity/nsp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NSP</a> to ensure their integrity.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"privacy\"><a href=\"#privacy\" aria-label=\"privacy permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Privacy</h2>\n<p>Ghost as an organisation is profitable, wholly independent, and only makes revenue directly from its customers. It has zero business interests of any kind predicated on selling private user data to third parties.</p>\n<p>In addition the Ghost software itself contains <a href=\"https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/PRIVACY.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">a plainly written summary</a> of every privacy-affecting feature within Ghost, along with detailed configuration options allowing any and all of them to be disabled at will.</p>\n<p>We take user privacy extremely seriously.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/concepts/security/"},"timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Ghost is committed to developing secure, reliable products utilising all modern security best practices and processes.The Ghost securityâ€¦","fileAbsolutePath":"C:/Users/bukharim96/Desktop/Projects/docs/content/concepts/security.md"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/concepts/security/"}}